name: Utricularia ariramba
remarks: doi:10.3897/phytokeys.169.57626 The specific epithet is a noun in apposition, referring to the Campos de Ariramba, where this species was discovered. The word 'ariramba' comes from the Tupi language 'uarirámba' and refers to the birds of the Galbulidae family, which are commonly found in the area.
